            <title>[SPARK-25786] If the ByteBuffer.hasArray is false , it will throw UnsupportedOperationException for Kryo</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-25786</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;`&lt;font color=&quot;#ffc66d&quot;&gt;deserialize&lt;/font&gt;` for kryo, &#160;the type of input parameter is ByteBuffer, if it is not backed by an accessible byte array. it will throw UnsupportedOperationException&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception Info:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException was thrown.&lt;br/&gt;
 java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException&lt;br/&gt;
 &#160;&#160; &#160;at java.nio.ByteBuffer.array(ByteBuffer.java:994)&lt;br/&gt;
 &#160;&#160; &#160;at org.apache.spark.serializer.KryoSerializerInstance.deserialize(KryoSerializer.scala:362)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
